posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: Are you connected to a school or corporate network?  It’s very common for github to be blocked on these networks.

posts.name: Joe Ross
posts.cooked: Can you access that link in a web browser?

posts.name: Alex Tsekhansky
posts.cooked: Yes, this really looks like a download error. As others said already, see if you can download the file it references directly in a browser on the same laptop
I had the same exact problem. What worked for us is installing the library online, un-installing it, and re installing it offline.
right now its telling me “no new dependances available” so im not sure what actual process to follow
we are on a school network
we could download it on a separate computer than move it over on a flash drive, or would that not work?

That also happened to us. It said that no new dependencies were available even though I knew that they were released shortly after kick off. If you don’t know what online importing is I would look it up because it is different from installing dependencies just using vs code. Once our team did the online import, it triggered the offline libraries to show up in vs
